OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1773324683
OL,3,CThe release of 400 million barrels of
OL,4,Coil is not enough to end the energy
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FThe reason energy prices are rising is
OL,8,Fsimple. The Strait of Hormuz - one of
OL,9,Fthe most important oil routes on the
OL,10,Fplanet - remains effectively closed.
OL,12,FOn a normal day, almost 200 oil and
OL,13,Fgas tankers pass through the narrow
OL,14,Fshipping lane between Iran and the
OL,15,FUnited Arab Emirates. It is the choke
OL,16,Fpoint through which a significant
OL,17,Fshare of the world's energy supply
OL,18,Fflows.
OL,20,FBut today, for a tenth consecutive
OL,21,Fday, barely anything moved.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1773324683
OL,3,CThe release of 400 million barrels of
OL,4,Coil is not enough to end the energy
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FOn Wednesday, barely any ships moved
OL,8,Fthrough the Strait of Hormuz according
OL,9,Fto this tracker by Marine Traffic.
OL,11,FWhen that happens, the effects cascade
OL,12,Fquickly through the energy system.
OL,13,FCountries in the Gulf cannot export.
OL,14,FStorage facilities start filling up.
OL,15,FAnd eventually production itself has
OL,16,Fto be cut.
OL,18,FThat is why the International Energy
OL,19,FAgency has agreed to release 400
OL,20,Fmillion barrels of emergency oil
OL,21,Fstocks.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
